gw.api.bean.compare

Class PropertyMatchPrioritizer<T extends KeyableBean>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.bean.compare.PropertyMatchPrioritizer<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<T>

    public class PropertyMatchPrioritizer<T extends KeyableBean>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<T>
    Comparator for prioritizing matches between beans based on the values of particular properties. An instance of this class is created for a particular reference bean, and then it is used to compare how well other beans match that bean. It is assumed, but not verified, that all beans passed to compare(gw.pl.persistence.core.entity.KeyableBean, gw.pl.persistence.core.entity.KeyableBean) actually do match the reference bean.
